Q.1.  When To Stop Testing (Exit Criteria In Software Testing)
> 1. When all our test cases was executed.
> 2. When application seems stable/bug free/ & Deadline also over.
> 3. When you Test plan Criteria's covered. 
> 4. When the project budget runs out
> 5. When we have reached an acceptable level of risk
> 6. When all the defects have been found.

